reviews.text:
Lovely place to stay in Hong Kong.

We had a week here, couldn't fault the facilities or service.

Our room was a good size, great view, comfortable bed, great air con. Fridge was a good size and worked well.

Staff were very friendly and efficient. The room servicing was very efficient.

Buffet breakfast was amazing, so much to choose from, all cooked perfectly. Good price.

Location is great, a wonderful shopping arcade right beside us, easy walking distance to the waterfront. 

The free shuttle service to their other hotel was great, every 20 minutes, close to heaps of shops, restaurants and services.

I'd be very happy to come back here, any time.
This is a great hotel, with everything you need. It is away from the main business districts, but has a free shuttle bus down town. There is a train station next door to take you anywhere.

Great place book club floor whatever you do book club floor.
A clearly underrated hotel.
Choose club floor.
Hotel is not far from metro.
Free shuttle bus down to Natan road.
Tremendous views from here.
Great staff.
A bargain regarding price 
Although not a new hotel its kept clean and nice that I can promise.

Expensive. Buffet breakfast is a waste, same thing every day. No help to carry luggage. Fresh fruit only once during the entire stay. Staff are rude, especially to Indians. Very near metro station. Good view of the harbour. Compared to other hotels value for money.

Though the property maybe good..the hotel does not provide basic microwave in deluxe rooms despite them being available for standard rooms. The hotel staff is obliged to be kind but when asked for assistance they more often straight away refuse. 
Hopefully the service attitude of staff improves (special mention to the people at the reception for being most uncourteous)
